GarrisonLeRockResume.pdf.job_description:
As a full stack Senior Software Engineer, you will be joining an elite team of technical powerhouses within our Keeper Dev team. Play a pivotal role designing, developing and maintaining our internal support tools used by Keeper employees. You will work closely with cross-functional teams to deliver high-quality software solutions that meet both user and business requirements.

Responsibilities

Own the ability to self-start and prioritize, plan, organize, and manage multiple tasks efficiently, in a demanding environment
Collaborate with product managers, designers, and other engineers to define and implement software solutions
Design, Develop, and maintain secure and scalable solutions for Keeper’s Support Tools
Utilize Java, MySQL, AWS, JavaScript
Balance multiple concurrent projects with varying priorities
Write clean, maintainable, and well documented code
Conduct code reviews
Troubleshoot and debug issues to ensure the performance, reliability, and security of applications
Excel at communicating with technical and non-technical teams
Stay up-to-date with emerging technologies and best practices in software development
Requirements
5+ years of professional experience in full-stack software development
Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science or equivalent discipline or equivalent experience
Strong experience with Java, JavaScript, HTML, CSS and popular frameworks/libraries (e.g., React, Angular, Vue.js).
Experience with database design and management (MySQL)
Familiarity with cloud platforms (AWS)
Excellent problem solving and communication skills
Proven ability to work in an agile development environment
Due to this role’s involvement in GovCloud, all applicants must be a US Person. A “U.S. Person” is defined as a U.S. citizen or a Lawful permanent resident (Green Card holder).”
GarrisonLeRockResume.pdf.recommendations: Your resume demonstrates strong security leadership and relevant cloud/DevOps experience, but it lacks explicit full-stack development in Java/JavaScript and MySQL, which are key for this Keeper role. To improve fit: - Add a concise “Full-Stack Experience” section or bullets that show direct work with Java, JavaScript, HTML/CSS, and a modern frontend framework (React/Angular/Vue). Include any MySQL or relational DB experience. - Highlight concrete, quantifiable outcomes from software development efforts (e.g., performance improvements, reduced defect rates, deployment speeds, security hardening metrics). - Reframe or add bullets that show collaboration with product managers, designers, and engineers in an agile environment, with code reviews and documentation. - Explicitly mention GovCloud eligibility or status (US Person) if applicable, since this is a compliance requirement. - Consider reorganizing to front-load relevant tech stack and project results, and add a few standalone projects or contributions that mirror Keeper’s internal support tools and security-focused features. A targeted rewrite could convert security leadership into concrete full-stack product development impact that aligns with the job description.
